3.65. 
Provisional measures of protection 
1. The court may, having regard to the interests of the children of the spouses as well as the interests of one of the spouses, impose provisional measures for their protection pending the decision of the court. 
2. The court may grant the following interim measures:
1) order one spouse to separate; 
2) establish the place of residence of the minor children with one of the parents; 
3) order one spouse not to interfere with the other spouse's use of certain property; 
4) order one spouse to pay temporary maintenance to the minor children or to the other spouse;
5) seize assets pending the resolution of the question of their ownership by one spouse, including for the purpose of securing the payment of maintenance; 6) seize the assets of one spouse, the value of which may be used to secure the reimbursement of the costs of the proceedings to the other spouse; 
7) prohibit one spouse from seeing the minor children or visiting certain places; 
8) such other measures as the court may deem necessary.
